{"hero":True,"sub":"Conflicts & Security","h3":"Iran warns ships over Hormuz route as US deal clock ticks","summary":"Iran called the new Strait of Hormuz transit route unacceptable and fired on a cargo ship as the 60-day window for a final US-Iran deal continues.","body":["Iran on June 25 called the newly designated Hormuz shipping route dangerous and warned vessels against transiting without clearance, US officials said, days after Iranian forces fired on a cargo ship in the strait. The flare-up tests a fragile memorandum of understanding signed by the US and Iranian presidents on June 17 to formally end the war within 60 days.","The deal reopened the strait, where roughly a fifth of global oil once flowed, and saw Washington lift its blockade on Iranian ports. Negotiators meeting in Switzerland agreed a road map toward a final accord and a communication line to prevent incidents, but the fate of Iran's nuclear program remains unresolved."],"sources":[("Times of Israel","https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog-june-25-2026/"),("Al Jazeera","https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/6/22/us-iran-agree-on-roadmap-towards-final-deal"),("NPR","https://www.npr.org/2026/06/21/g-s1-129222/us-iran-deal-lebanon-israel-strait-hormuz-jd-vance")]},
{"sub":"Conflicts & Security","h3":"Ukraine strikes deep into Russia as Crimea losses mount","summary":"Kyiv hit Russian air defenses and military airfields in occupied Crimea and struck a Moscow refinery, with the SBU calling the peninsula a zone of constant losses.","body":["Ukraine's security service said Crimea has become a zone of constant losses after a series of strikes on Russian air defenses and military airfields. Kyiv also launched a major drone attack on Gazprom's Moscow refinery, triggering a large explosion and bringing the war's costs home to Russian cities.","Analysts say a run of deep-strike successes has revived hopes the war could be shifting in Ukraine's favor, with rising desertion among Russian troops as advances stall. They warn, however, that Ukraine's pressure campaign risks provoking fresh Russian escalation."],"sources":[("Kyiv Independent","https://kyivindependent.com/ukraine-war-latest-crimea-now-zone-of-constant-losses-sbu-says-after-strikes-on-russian-air-defenses-military-airfields/"),("Al Jazeera","https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/6/25/as-ukraine-seizes-first-chance-to-win-war-horrors-come-home-to-russia"),("CNBC","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/06/24/ukraine-russia-drone-strikes-moscow-escalation.html")]},
{"sub":"Conflicts & Security","h3":"RSF drone barrage hits El Obeid as UN warns of atrocities","summary":"Sudan's RSF launched fresh drone strikes on El Obeid after knocking out the city's power, as the Security Council warned of an imminent risk of mass atrocities.","body":["The Rapid Support Forces launched a new wave of drone strikes on El Obeid hours after an attack on the city's main power transformer caused a blackout, capping a week of daily bombardment of the North Kordofan capital. The UN envoy for Sudan pressed RSF leader Mohamed Hamdan Daglo for de-escalation in a phone call.","The Security Council urged the RSF to halt its assault and warned of an imminent risk of mass atrocities. Sudan remains the world's largest displacement crisis, with the UN refugee agency reporting a 72 percent funding deficit for its response."],"sources":[("OCHA","https://www.unocha.org/news/todays-top-news-global-humanitarian-overview-2026-sudan-occupied-palestinian-territory"),("CFR","https://www.cfr.org/global-conflict-tracker/conflict/power-struggle-sudan")]},
{"sub":"Conflicts & Security","h3":"Taiwan tests rapid wartime footing as PLA pressure grows","summary":"Taiwan launched a combat readiness exercise to test fast mobilization as China said its Liaoning carrier completed more than 40 days of drills.","body":["Taiwan began an immediate combat readiness exercise designed to test rapid movement to a wartime footing as Chinese air and naval operations compress its response times. The drills come as Beijing said its Liaoning aircraft carrier had completed over 40 days of exercises in the region.","The maneuvers add to a tense security picture across East Asia, where sustained PLA activity around the island has pushed Taipei to rehearse faster mobilization of its forces."],"sources":[("AEI","https://www.aei.org/articles/china-taiwan-update-june-5-2026/"),("The Asia Cable","https://www.theasiacable.com/p/asia-daily-june-23-2026")]},
{"sub":"Diplomacy & Trade","h3":"G7 in France praises Iran deal and pledges tougher Russia sanctions","summary":"Trump signed the US-Iran memorandum at the G7 summit in France as allies pushed Ukraine back up the agenda and pledged stronger sanctions on Moscow.","body":["At the Group of Seven summit in Evian-les-Bains, President Trump digitally signed the memorandum of understanding setting out terms to end the US-Iran war, including reopening the Strait of Hormuz and lifting sanctions on Tehran. A joint statement, notable for US participation, praised the agreement and pledged tougher sanctions on Russia.","Host President Emmanuel Macron said he would press Trump to keep backing Ukraine and to increase pressure on Moscow toward a peace deal, as allies worked to return the war to the top of the agenda after more than four years of fighting."],"sources":[("CNN","https://www.cnn.com/2026/06/17/world/live-news/iran-war-g7-summit"),("NBC News","https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/live-blog/live-updates-trump-g7-summit-iran-deal-russia-ukraine-war-iran-israel-rcna350404"),("NPR","https://www.npr.org/2026/06/16/g-s1-128325/g7-leaders-summit")]},
{"sub":"Diplomacy & Trade","h3":"EU moves to slash steel quotas as China export surge bites","summary":"Brussels will cut tariff-free steel quotas by 47 percent and double out-of-quota duties from July, as it edges toward its own Section 301-style response to China.","body":["Beginning in July the EU will cut tariff-free steel quotas by 47 percent, from roughly 33 million tonnes to 18.3 million, and double out-of-quota duties from 25 to 50 percent through 2031. The move reflects mounting frustration as cheap Chinese cars, batteries, steel and electronics flood European markets.","What began as a debate over Chinese electric vehicles has broadened into a confrontation over China's industrial overcapacity. Germany is losing about 10,000 manufacturing jobs a month amid the intensifying competition, and Brussels is weighing tools modeled on the US Section 301 process."],"sources":[("Atlantic Council","https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/dispatches/europe-has-had-enough-of-chinas-export-surge/"),("Atlantic Council","https://www.atlanticcouncil.org/blogs/econographics/as-chinas-surpluses-become-unbearable-the-eu-is-edging-toward-its-own-section-301/")]},
{"sub":"Diplomacy & Trade","h3":"Gulf states press Iran on missiles and proxies for lasting peace","summary":"Gulf foreign ministers said Iran's proxies and missiles must be addressed for durable peace as US Secretary of State Rubio toured Arab allies.","body":["Gulf foreign ministers said Iran's proxy networks and missile arsenal must be addressed for any lasting peace, even as the US-Iran interim deal moves forward. US Secretary of State Marco Rubio met Bahrain's King Hamad bin Isa al-Khalifa on June 25 during a tour to brief Arab Gulf partners on the agreement.","The diplomacy underscores Gulf concerns that an end to the US-Iran war must not leave regional security questions unresolved, with the strait's reopening and demining among the immediate priorities."],"sources":[("Jerusalem Post","https://www.jpost.com/middle-east/iran-news/2026-06-25/live-updates-900444"),("Times of Israel","https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog-june-25-2026/")]},
{"sub":"Diplomacy & Trade","h3":"US-China deal holds 30 percent tariffs as new probe looms","summary":"A June trade deal kept existing US tariffs on China at 30 percent and paused higher levies, while a new Section 301 forced-labor tariff was proposed.","body":["A trade deal announced in June left in place the current 20 percent fentanyl and 10 percent reciprocal US tariffs on China, a combined 30 percent, while pausing higher tariffs for 60 days. The US Trade Representative separately proposed a new 12.5 percent tariff tied to a Section 301 investigation into forced labor.","Analysts say the Trump tariffs amount to the largest US tax increase as a share of GDP since 1993, equivalent to about 1,500 dollars per household in 2026, keeping trade tensions front and center for the global economy."],"sources":[("Tax Foundation","https://taxfoundation.org/research/all/federal/trump-tariffs-trade-war/"),("China Briefing","https://www.china-briefing.com/news/us-china-tariff-rates-2025/")]},
{"sub":"Diplomacy & Trade","h3":"Macron's domestic weakness erodes France's clout in Brussels","summary":"France's political fragmentation has sapped Macron's influence in the EU, seen in his failure to block the Mercosur trade deal.","body":["France has been paralyzed by political fragmentation and partisan infighting since the 2024 dissolution of the National Assembly, and diplomats say the bloc's second-largest member is losing influence in Brussels. Macron's inability to assemble a blocking minority against the Mercosur deal underscored how his weakened position at home undercuts his leverage in the EU.","The government is also struggling to rein in soaring debt and deficits, and Macron replaced his commissioner with Stephane Sejourne, who is viewed as carrying less weight than his predecessor."],"sources":[("Euronews","https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2026/01/09/mercosur-how-macrons-domestic-weakness-undercut-his-brussels-clout")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"Record heat dome bakes Europe as France logs hottest day","summary":"A severe second heatwave in two months pushed France to its hottest day on record, with at least 48 drowning deaths and widespread power outages.","body":["A heat dome that settled over Europe on June 17 drove France to its hottest day on record, with the national average reaching 29.8C and one town topping 44C. At least 48 people drowned seeking relief from the heat, two young children died in a hot car, and tens of thousands lost power as the grid strained.","Western Europe bore the brunt, with records falling across France, the UK and Ireland. Hundreds of schools closed or shortened hours and rail travel was discouraged, while scientists said the climate crisis is making such heatwaves more frequent and intense."],"sources":[("Al Jazeera","https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/6/24/deaths-disruptions-across-europe-what-you-should-know-about-the-heatwave"),("CNN","https://www.cnn.com/2026/06/23/climate/europe-heat-wave-france-uk-spain"),("Time","https://time.com/article/2026/06/23/heatwave-europe-record-high-temperatures-deadly-extreme-heat-stress-safety/")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"Gaza reconstruction barely begun as needs hit 71 billion dollars","summary":"A UN and EU assessment put Gaza recovery needs at 71.4 billion dollars over a decade, with just 0.5 percent of rubble cleared under a fragile ceasefire.","body":["The Security Council heard that the tenuous Gaza ceasefire must be consolidated as a final UN and EU damage and needs assessment estimated recovery costs at 71.4 billion dollars over the next decade. Nearly the entire population of 1.8 million remains displaced and dependent on aid.","Progress has barely started, with only 0.5 percent of rubble cleared and most donor pledges yet to reach the World Bank-administered reconstruction fund. The second phase of Trump's 20-point plan, aimed at demilitarization and rebuilding, is now under way with support from countries including Bahrain and Pakistan."],"sources":[("UN Press","https://press.un.org/en/2026/sc16284.doc.htm"),("UN","https://www.un.org/unispal/document/amid-a-tenuous-ceasefire-and-soaring-humanitarian-needs-the-security-council-hears-updates-on-transitional-governance-structures-and-reconstruction-efforts-in-gaza/")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"DR Congo crisis deepens with appeal only 30 percent funded","summary":"Humanitarian conditions in eastern DR Congo keep deteriorating amid ongoing violence, with the 1.4 billion dollar appeal critically underfunded.","body":["Conditions in the eastern provinces of Ituri, North Kivu and South Kivu continue to deteriorate as violence persists, the UN reported. The 1.4 billion dollar humanitarian response plan for the country remains only about 30 percent funded.","The shortfall compounds one of the world's most severe and protracted displacement emergencies, straining aid agencies trying to reach civilians caught in the fighting."],"sources":[("OCHA","https://www.unocha.org/news/todays-top-news-global-humanitarian-overview-2026-sudan-occupied-palestinian-territory"),("UNHCR","https://www.unhcr.org/us/emergencies/dr-congo-emergency")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"Israel-Hezbollah talks stall over disarmament and withdrawals","summary":"Sporadic Israel-Hezbollah fighting continued into late June as talks snagged on disarming the group and mutual withdrawal from southern Lebanon.","body":["Fighting between Israel and Hezbollah continued into June even as negotiations sought a durable arrangement. Sticking points include the disarmament of Hezbollah and a mutual withdrawal of forces from southern Lebanon.","The friction adds another flashpoint to a region absorbing the aftermath of the US-Iran war and the fragile Gaza ceasefire, keeping the prospect of renewed escalation alive."],"sources":[("Jerusalem Post","https://www.jpost.com/middle-east/iran-news/2026-06-25/live-updates-900444"),("CNN","https://www.cnn.com/world/middleeast/israel")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"Russia's economy strains as inflation doubts and unrest grow","summary":"Putin has hinted at peace talks as Russia's economy buckles, with independent estimates putting true inflation far above the official 5.6 percent.","body":["President Putin has signaled openness to peace talks as economic pressure mounts, with people fleeing some cities and reports of toxic oil rains near damaged facilities. Russia's official inflation stood at 5.6 percent year on year in mid-June, but Swedish intelligence alleged the real figure could be as high as 15 percent.","The strain coincides with a stalled battlefield advance and rising desertion requests among Russian troops, factors analysts say are feeding domestic discontent as Ukraine intensifies deep strikes."],"sources":[("Al Jazeera","https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/6/25/as-ukraine-seizes-first-chance-to-win-war-horrors-come-home-to-russia"),("CNBC","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/06/24/ukraine-russia-drone-strikes-moscow-escalation.html")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"Japan and South Korea keep thaw but stop short of new deals","summary":"Tokyo and Seoul have preserved their rapprochement under new leaders but have yet to convert stability into major fresh cooperation.","body":["Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi and President Lee Jae Myung have maintained the rapprochement built by their predecessors but have not turned that stability into significant new cooperation. Analysts point to economic coordination and possible South Korean accession to the CPTPP as openings.","Lingering obstacles include Japanese restrictions tied to Fukushima seafood and domestic political sensitivities in both capitals, leaving the relationship steady but cautious."],"sources":[("The Asia Cable","https://www.theasiacable.com/p/asia-daily-june-23-2026")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"Gaza coordination center overhauled to hold fragile truce","summary":"The civil-military coordination center in Kiryat Gat is being revamped to strengthen ceasefire monitoring, aid entry and postwar planning for Gaza.","body":["The Civil-Military Coordination Center in Kiryat Gat is undergoing an overhaul to strengthen its role monitoring the Israel-Hamas ceasefire, facilitating aid into Gaza and developing postwar policy. The body has become central to managing a truce that remains fragile.","Israeli strikes and armed activity by Hamas and other groups have continued to test the agreement, even after the body of the last Israeli hostage in Gaza was recovered, underscoring the difficulty of stabilizing the enclave."],"sources":[("Times of Israel","https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog-june-25-2026/"),("UN Press","https://press.un.org/en/2026/sc16284.doc.htm")]},
{"sub":"Humanitarian & Climate","h3":"France restricts public water use as grid buckles in heat","summary":"France imposed water restrictions and battled power outages as a second heat-dome event in two months hit France, the UK and Spain.","body":["France restricted public water use as the country sweltered under what officials called a heat-dome driven furnace, the second such event in two months. Power outages spread as demand surged and infrastructure buckled under the extreme temperatures.","The crisis stretched across France, the UK and Spain, raising concerns about energy and water supplies and prompting health warnings for vulnerable populations as the heatwave persisted."],"sources":[("CNN","https://www.cnn.com/2026/06/22/climate/europe-heat-wave-dome-france-uk-spain"),("Al Jazeera","https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/6/24/power-outage-in-france-as-europe-bakes-in-record-heat")]},
{"sub":"Diplomacy & Trade","h3":"Trump derails party win to force elections overhaul vote","summary":"On June 25 President Trump undercut a likely win for his party to push lawmakers toward an elections overhaul bill stalled in the Senate.","body":["President Trump on June 25 undercut what could have been a victory for his own party, using the move to pressure lawmakers into advancing an elections overhaul bill that has been all but doomed in the Senate. The maneuver injected fresh turmoil into Washington's legislative agenda.","The clash came days after New York's primaries, where progressives backed by Mayor Zohran Mamdani swept safe seats while moderates prevailed in competitive ones, sharpening a debate over how far left the Democratic Party should move."],"sources":[("NPR","https://www.npr.org/sections/elections/")]}
